parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line corrosion can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake fluid leaking from a loose line
corrosion on the brake line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS module failure can cause the anti-lock braking system to malfunction, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: ABS system inoperable
ABS warning light on the dashboard
module runs continuously
fuse needs to be pulled to shut off the system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Hydroboost unit leaking can cause the brakes to hang up and the pedal not to return to its normal position, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Brakes hang up
pedal does not return to its normal position
hydroboost unit leaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal issues can cause difficulty stopping the vehicle, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire issues can cause loss of control or accidents, especially when driving on gravel roads.
symptoms: Tires punctured by rocks
frequent flat tires
tires need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Tires make a noise
pieces of rubber fall off
tire tread partially or completely separates
tire fails while driving
uneven tread wear
substantial cracking throughout the tread.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spare tire failure and detachment can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Spare tire falls off while driving
spare tire damages surrounding components (e.g.
trailer axle
tire rim)
spare tire is not properly secured.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Manufacturer and Dealer Response to Tire Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of manufacturers and dealers to respond to tire issues can lead to continued use of defective tires, potentially causing accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Manufacturers and dealers fail to return phone calls
refuse to provide assistance
or only offer to replace tires with the same make and model
despite safety concerns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The throttle sticks
the vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the engine fails to decelerate upon release of the accelerator
the vehicle maintains a high RPM for 5-10 seconds
additional braking is required to slow down
sudden acceleration while the vehicle is parked.
